  24 Jun 2010; Justin Lecher <jlec@gentoo.org> mafft-6.240-r1.ebuild,
  mafft-6.707.ebuild, mafft-6.811.ebuild:
  Fix installpath for manpages, #278571

*mafft-6.811 (15 Jun 2010)

  15 Jun 2010; Justin Lecher <jlec@gentoo.org> +files/6.811-respect.patch,
  +mafft-6.811.ebuild:
  Version BUmp, keyworded for prefix, repecting multilib and LDFLAGS

*mafft-6.707 (27 Jul 2009)

  27 Jul 2009; Donnie Berkholz <dberkholz@gentoo.org>; +mafft-6.707.ebuild:
  Bump to latest. Use no-extensions version because the extensions rely on a
  bunch of bundled packages. That means you don't get RNA structural
  alignment, sorry.

  27 Jul 2009; Donnie Berkholz <dberkholz@gentoo.org>;
  mafft-6.240-r1.ebuild:
  Keyword ~amd64.

*mafft-6.240-r1 (23 Sep 2008)

  23 Sep 2008; Markus Dittrich <markusle@gentoo.org>
  +files/mafft-6.240-mktemp.patch, -mafft-5.861-r1.ebuild,
  -mafft-6.240.ebuild, +mafft-6.240-r1.ebuild:
  Added patch to fix insecure tempfile handling (see bug #235804). 
  Removed ebuilds for vulnerable versions.

  08 Oct 2007; Markus Dittrich <markusle@gentoo.org> mafft-5.861-r1.ebuild, +mafft-6.240.ebuild:
  Fixed wrongs SRC_URI and HOMEPAGE (see bug #195080). Also bumped
  package to the most recent version.

*mafft-5.861-r1 (09 Nov 2006)

  09 Nov 2006; Donnie Berkholz <dberkholz@gentoo.org>; -mafft-5.861.ebuild,
  +mafft-5.861-r1.ebuild:
  (#154545) Install to correct locations and set PREFIX so it finds the
  binaries automatically.

*mafft-5.861 (21 Oct 2006)

  21 Oct 2006; Donnie Berkholz <dberkholz@gentoo.org>; +metadata.xml,
  +mafft-5.861.ebuild:
  New package: Multiple sequence alignments using a variety of algorithms.

